rComments: A truly phenomenal professor. His lectures were a balance of meticulous preparation on his part and spontaneous in-class discussions. He engages students and is one of the most encouraging professors I've ever had. His analysis was thoroughly insightful and I left every class feeling like I learnt something valuable. Brilliant.

He's absolutely wonderful and really cool in general. He's helpful in office hours and you can even talk to him after class. He helped me out with another course as well, because we were discussing a similar topic.

Phil is such a nice guy and I always left his lectures with a new perspective on the texts. In the lectures, he balances asserting his reading of the text as well as offering a general basis for interpretation. He doesn't spoon feed you interpretations but provides you with more than enough tools to develop your own readings. Awesome teacher.
He is available for students, always there to help and listen. He looks forward rather than backward, which is refreshing. Great guy!
